description:
This one shot is double length and made up for two stories (Cry No more / Shattered Mirrors) that follow on from each other.

Nicole visits a place from her past and it brings back memories of her child hood and her mother who passed away while she was still young. Her father is great with her and her sister until his past catches up with him and he is gunned down in their home. Von Drake delivers the fatal blow and kidnaps her sister.

The young Nicole is institutionalized and becomes increasingly violent and is abused by a member of staff until she fights back and escapes the building. She's helped by a hooker who gets her back on her feet and on her first trick she kills the john as soon as he touches her.

Back in the present day Razor is in an apartment waiting for the owner. He turns out to be the orderly that raped her. She cripples him and then takes his arms carving 'rapist' onto his forehead.

name: Jughead

description:
The best-selling title by blockbuster new talent Sanbe Kei (Kamiyadori)! In a dark future, rival warriors of warring sects persecute nonbelievers and die for their faith. But a disillusioned young novice and a deadly gun-toting priest may be about to change all that…

Young Capria has completed her studies at the Arsenal School and has begun her internship with the Elysia Unification Council under Father Garrincha. But no lessons could prepare this sheltered novice for the outside world, where rebels battle against the dreaded "Testarotho." Heretics are tried and burned at the stake, warring religious factions battle for power, and the common people live a miserable life in feudal servitude. Can she bring a spark of hope to a world filled with destruction and madness? Maybe if she lives long enough!

description: Note: This is the second appearance of Cheryl Blossom and her brother, Jason. While this issue has the same cover date as Cheryl's first appearance in Betty And Veronica # 320, she is featured on the Betty And Veronica cover as "Introducing", therefore that issue is commonly referred to as her introduction.
name: Barely Friendly

description: Converting heretics to the church of Arsenal is a difficult and sometimes deadly task, and Inquisitor Garrincha is the best Neo Arsen has to offer. It's no wonder the man has scores of enemies among non-believers and those faithful to his church. When an entire village of heretics is found dead, Garrincha and his entourage are brutally captured, and he's charged with the massacre. Now, freeing him and clearing his name is up to his fiercely loyal Rotho, led by the gun-slinging Leonedus — but what if he doesn't make it in time?

Leoneduss master is dead, his friends lost, his eyes blinded, and now his own people are trying to assassinate him. Trapped behind enemy lines, he and Capria find solace where they least expect itwith the very Materia rebels they came to exterminate. All his life, Leonedus has performed his duty. Now, the outcast priest must learn to see with his heart what his eyes cannot.

The action reaches fever pitch in this pulse-pounding final volume! When Materia's top leaders are captured by Arsenal assassins, it's up to Leonedus to stand against his former masters. The trail of blood Leonedus has left in his life runs deep — can he continue to kill now that he's found his conscience?
